				<li id="16507399" class="cmnt-root" data="3" data-d="1647254125000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="https://fextralife.com/avatars/132087_1647250171.png" alt="" /><a class="comment-username" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&u=132087" rel="nofollow"  target="_blank" style="color: #;">AlatarXarxes</a></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578318/Magic-Glintblade" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">14 Mar 2022 06:35</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16507399" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">This spell has a bug when used in sequence casting (this spell used in a follow up cast)<br/><br/>If Glintblade is the third spell cast in a sequence (from a glintstone spell such as pebble)  its animation will display and then the sword will not fire, creating a visual bug in the air.<br/><br/>This will ALWAYS bug if it is cast using the characters left to right staff animation.<br/><br/>To replicate this, simply cast  glintstone pebble  x2 and then magic glintblade.<br/>It can consistently bug if cast in this order.<br/>Pebble x2, glint, pebble, glint, pebble as each time glint is cast, it is during the left to right staff animation.<br/></p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16507399" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16507399" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies 